<p>I'm trying to make an image go through a blur effect using CSS keyframes, but for some reason when animation gets put into the mix I can't get it to work.</p>  <p>I can get it to work without animation, similar to this example <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12224320/defined-edges-with-css3-filter-blur">Defined Edges With CSS3 Filter Blur</a>, but again not with animation. Here's the code I'm working with. Ideas?</p>  <p><br /><br /> <strong><a href="http://codepen.io/anon/pen/GpqoqK" rel="nofollow">See Codepen DEMO here</a></strong> <br /> <br /><br /></p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>body {background-color: black; padding: 100px;} .wrapper {overflow:hidden !important;} .background-image {   width: 500px;    height: 200px;   margin: -20px;   background: url(https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1439396087961-98bc12c21176?q=80&amp;fm=jpg&amp;s=bce7579fe32b464cc2d53c5c144a2de4);   background-size: 100%;   -webkit-animation: filter-animation 10s infinite;}  @-webkit-keyframes filter-animation { 0% {-webkit-filter: blur(0px);} 25% {-webkit-filter: blur(2px);} 50% {-webkit-filter: blur(20px);} 75% {-webkit-filter: blur(2px);} 100% {-webkit-filter: blur(0px);}}</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;div class"wrapper"&gt;   &lt;div class="background-image"&gt;   &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>